Sentencas: A single-step wet-chemical synthesis of NiO-SDC (Sm3+ doped ceria) colloidal ink for the inkjet printing (IJP) of nanostructured anodic layers with enhanced catalytic activity for solid oxide fuel cells (SOFCs) is developed and characterized.
Titulo: Nanostructured engineering of nickel cermet anode for solid oxide fuel cell using inkjet printing

Sentencas: Dynamic light scattering, scanning electron microscope, and Raman spectroscopy revealed stable nanoparticles with the main size of 11.85 nm within the ink solution.
Titulo: Nanostructured engineering of nickel cermet anode for solid oxide fuel cell using inkjet printing

Sentencas: Rheology parameters were analyzed, and the anode was printed.
Titulo: Nanostructured engineering of nickel cermet anode for solid oxide fuel cell using inkjet printing

Sentencas: Porous post-sintered Ni-cermet layer, with a thickness of 15-25 ?m contained nearspherical nanoparticles of 40-80 nm, was obtained.
Titulo: Nanostructured engineering of nickel cermet anode for solid oxide fuel cell using inkjet printing

Sentencas: X-ray diffraction confirmed the phase composition of the cermet layer.
Titulo: Nanostructured engineering of nickel cermet anode for solid oxide fuel cell using inkjet printing

Sentencas: Electrical impedance spectroscopy demonstrated a significant reduction, by more than 80 %, in the area-specific resistance of the IJP half-cell in comparison with the Screen-printed half-cell.
Titulo: Nanostructured engineering of nickel cermet anode for solid oxide fuel cell using inkjet printing

Sentencas: The microstructure engineering using IJP provides fabrication of the cermet NiO-SDC layer with a conjugated structure, which ultimately enhances the catalytic activity of the SOFC.
Titulo: Nanostructured engineering of nickel cermet anode for solid oxide fuel cell using inkjet printing
